➤ Sheltered Under Eagles Wings
https://www.amazingfacts.org/media-library/media/e/4296/f/6/t/sheltered-under-eagles-wings

The world’s longest commercial flight is from Dubai to New Zealand, covering more than 8,800 miles and lasting about 17 hours. That’s a really long trip, especially if you have the middle seat. Yet that is nothing compared to how long some birds can stay aloft. Take the Common Swift for example...
